{"key":"processedPost-9617910","value":{"id":9617910,"first":9611203,"last":9617910,"when":1232081961,"utime":"01/16/09 06:59 AM","cleanedPost":"Mini-greenhouses are hard to maintain upper 90% humidity in, thus they're better suited for tray culture.&nbsp; If you're going to use it for cakes, I'd put them on an upper shelf.&nbsp; In my experience from having hygrometers on every shelf, humidity is higher on upper shelves than on lower ones.&nbsp; Put the cakes closer together, and get a tray of damp perlite directly under them.&nbsp; Mist often, but make sure the ultrasonic output doesn't spray directly on them.&nbsp; You want some drying between mistings.<br />RR"}}